[[Image:Poslowie Barry Kent.PNG|thumb|right|200px|Number of seats taken by constituencies. Number of active voters per 1 seat ([[Polish parliamentary election, 2007]])]] '''Electoral districts of Poland''' ({{lang-pl|okręg wyborczy}}) are defined by [[Polish law|Polish]] [[election law]]. Electoral districts can be divided depending on whether they are individual entities or parts of a larger electoral district with regard to elections to 1) parliament ([[Sejm]]) and [[Senate of Poland|Senate]] 2) local offices and 3) [[European Parliament]]. Each district has a number of [[Mandate (politics)|mandates]] calculated on the basis of its population.
