The '''Pears Institute for the Study of Antisemitism''' was launched in 2010,<ref>{{cite web|author=Connected Worlds Web Design Norwich |url=http://www.pearsfoundation.org.uk/news/inaugural-lecture-launches-pears-institute-study-antisemitism/ |title=@ Pears Foundation |website=Pearsfoundation.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2017-03-28}}</ref> as a centre for research, teaching, and public policy formation relating to [[antisemitism]] and racial intolerance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pearsinstitute.bbk.ac.uk/ |title=Home &#124; Pears Institute for the Study of Antisemitism |website=Pearsinstitute.bbk.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2017-03-28}}</ref>
The Institute is based at [[Birkbeck College|Birkbeck]], University of London, and was established by the [[Pears Foundation]]. The director is [[David Feldman (historian)|David Feldman]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thejc.com/news/uk-news/labour-inquiry-professor-has-links-to-group-that-says-antisemitism-claims-are-baseless-1.56380 |title=Labour inquiry professor has links to group that says antisemitism claims are "baseless" |website=Thejc.com |accessdate=2017-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://impact.ref.ac.uk/CaseStudies/CaseStudy.aspx?Id=18945 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2017-03-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170329051035/http://impact.ref.ac.uk/CaseStudies/CaseStudy.aspx?Id=18945 |archivedate=2017-03-29 |df= }} </ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thecommentator.com/article/3795/conference_on_bds_campaign_against_israel_to_be_held_in_london |title=Conference on BDS campaign against Israel to be held in London |publisher=The Commentator |date=2013-06-17 |accessdate=2017-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Reisz |first=Matthew |url=https://www.timeshighereducation.com/news/labour-party-anti-semitism-inquiry-academic-david-feldman-on-being-caught-in-a-storm |title=Labour anti-Semitism inquiry academic on being caught in a storm |website=Timeshighereducation.com |date= |accessdate=2017-03-28}}</ref>
